HEADWORD: Remanency
<hw>Rem"a*nen*cy</hw> <pr>(-n<it>e</it>n*s?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. OF. <ets>remanence</ets>, LL. <ets>remanentia</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>remanens</ets>. See <er>Remanent</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<def>The state of being remanent; continuance; permanence.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>remanence</qex> of the will in the fallen spirit.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

